In any case -- the idea of a Druid Rocket Scientist does not seem all that odd, to me. But I have grown up around Pagans. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://thilandrae.clanpages.com/taranissig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mauk2>Mauk2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/27/02 4:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rocket Scientists and Druids.</span><hr size=1> Nuclear is Natural! <br>
